{"word":"ὀδυνάω","slug":"ὀδυνάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀδυνάω</b></el> <el>(ὀδῠνάω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, 2nd sg. <el>ὀδυνᾶσαι</el> in <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>\n<p/><i>to cause</i> one <i>pain</i> or <i>suffering, to distress</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to feel pain, suffer pain</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>ἃ ὠδυνήθην</el> <i>the pains I suffered</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b> <p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὀδύνη'><el>ὀδύνη</el></a>\n"}]}